                            'title' => 'James Bond Style Rules – Menswear Secrets from 007',
                            'description' => '<p>James Bond is one of the world&rsquo;s most famous fictional characters. His style is admired, copied, and adored by men around the world. Even though there are entire blogs and channels dedicated to the style of James Bond, it&rsquo;s not that easy to copy his look because on the one hand, you need a lot of dough, and on the other hand, you may not look like James Bond.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Just because an outfit works well for 007, doesn&rsquo;t mean it will work well for you, and your style, and your surroundings. At the Gentleman&rsquo;s Gazette, we think it makes more sense to figure out what style rules Bond abides by and then use those to adapt them to your unique situations rather than just copying him to the tee.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xsZ5QBGkWfo/hqdefault.jpg" style="height:360px; width:480px" /></p>

<h2>The Evolution of Agent 007&rsquo;s Style</h2>

<p>Agent 007 has been on film since 1962 when Sean Connery embodied Bond in Doctor No. Bond is now entering his seventh decade at Hollywood and as you can imagine, his style has changed quite a bit throughout the years. Bond has worn everything from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/dinner-jacket-black-tie-guide/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="">dinner jackets</a>&nbsp;to traditional tuxedos, Scottish Highland dress, formal&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/morning-dress-dress-code/">morning dress</a>, as well as one-piece ski suits in&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/how-wear-yellow-menswear/">yellow</a>, as well as tropical shirts.</p>

<p>While James bond was a fan of disguises, which luckily the current one is not really a fan of anymore, instead he has developed a sartorial reputation that shows him as being effortlessly dapper at all times, always prepared for the situation, and dress appropriately. And of course, Bond has worn many bad outfits and admiring them or imitating them is just not stylish at all. For example, in the 1970s, it was, in general, a really dark era for classic men&rsquo;s style and fashion and that was also true for Bond.</p>

<p>Ian Fleming&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/literary-james-bond-original-007/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="">literary James Bond</a>&nbsp;was not nearly as stylish as he is made out to be today. Of course, over the course of two dozens of Bond films, different costume designers and choreographers have changed the way he looked. On top of that, product placements play a much bigger role today than they used to be 40 years ago. So just because Bond now drinks Heineken and shaves with a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/the-gillette-ad-and-the-modern-gentleman/">Gillette</a>, doesn&rsquo;t mean that you should.</p>

<p>Daniel Craig has been playing Bond since 2006 and he definitely has brought him into a new era of Bond style.</p>

<h2>What Are James Bond&rsquo;s Style Rules?</h2>

<p>Even though we think it&rsquo;s impossible to distill the James Bond-style down to one single concept, we came up with 11 rules that we think he lives by.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Daniel-Craig-as-James-Bond-in-black-suit.jpg"><img alt="Daniel Craig as James Bond in black suit" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Daniel-Craig-as-James-Bond-in-black-suit-1030x1030.jpg" style="height:1030px; width:1030px" /></a></p>

<p>Daniel Craig as James Bond in black suit</p>

<h2>1. He Respects The Power and Style Of Clothes</h2>

<p>Obviously, Bond is an intense character who&rsquo;s more a man of action rather than words. As such, his clothes are an important part of who he is and how he wants to be perceived.</p>

<p>In the 2006 Casino Royale movie, we can see that Bond utilizes his clothes as a tool. In the opening scene, he wears a tropical shirt whereas later in the movies, Vesper comments on his disdain for the suit and later on, he changes his dinner jacket for a traditional&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/tuxedo-black-tie-guide/advanced/james-bond-tuxedo/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="">tuxedo</a>. By the end of the movie, Bond is embracing the power of clothes, wearing a three-piece&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/how-many-suits-does-a-man-need/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="">suit</a>&nbsp;for his final show of power. There&rsquo;s no real purpose for this outfit other than showing that Bond has fully grasped the power of clothes and his new identity. Bond fully understands that great clothes, especially more formal ones such as a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/how-to-pair-shirts-ties-with-blue-suits/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="">suit</a>, add to his air of competence and authority. He fully understands that he&rsquo;s not going to earn respect or elicit fear if he&rsquo;s dressed like the average American suburban dad.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/50-Years-of-James-Bond-Tuxedos.jpg"><img alt="50 Years of James Bond Tuxedos" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/50-Years-of-James-Bond-Tuxedos-1030x687.jpg" style="height:687px; width:1030px" /></a></p>

<p>50 Years of James Bond Tuxedos</p>

<h2>2. He Knows What Works for Him and Sticks With It</h2>

<p>What does that mean? Well, he expects his garments to perform and so he doesn&rsquo;t use cheap substitutes. He also keeps his color palette somewhat limited to keep a harmonious look that is somewhat of a signature for him.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/James-Bond-in-brown-sahntung-silk-Nehru-jacket.webp"><img alt="James Bond in brown sahntung silk Nehru jacket" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/James-Bond-in-brown-sahntung-silk-Nehru-jacket-900x898.webp" style="height:898px; width:900px" /></a></p>

<p>James Bond in brown shantung silk Nehru jacket</p>

<h2>3. Bond&rsquo;s Style Never Overshadows Him</h2>

<p>The same is true for you, the clothes shouldn&rsquo;t be wearing you, you should be wearing your clothes. That means the clothes shouldn&rsquo;t be so bold that they overshadow your&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/10-ways-to-find-your-personal-style/">personality</a>. Bond has understood that and he keeps it simple. Bond sticks with muted colors, white shirts, subtle&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/pattern-matching-good-taste-test/">patterns</a>, and nothing is overdone. Obviously, his style is deliberately not flashy at all.&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Tom-Ford-suits-in-James-Bond-films.webp"><img alt="Tom Ford suits in James Bond films" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Tom-Ford-suits-in-James-Bond-films-900x600.webp" style="height:600px; width:900px" /></a></p>

<p>Tom Ford suits in James Bond films</p>

<h2>4. Bond Moves With The Times But Leans Into Classics</h2>

<p>Fashion has changed radically since 1962 and every Bond has found a way to move with the fashions. Roger Moore wore a safari suit and flared&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/features-of-a-pair-of-pants/">pants</a>&nbsp;in the 1970s, Pierce Brosnan&rsquo;s Brioni suits and jackets lean more into the looser fit of the 90s versus Daniel Craig in the 2000s used&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/gentleman-style-tom-ford/">Tom Ford</a>&nbsp;suits with a slimmer and trimmer silhouette. So even though Bond goes with the time, certain elements like the classic suit are always part of his repertoire.</p>

<p>The same is true for you, you don&rsquo;t have to buy period garments but you can buy items that you can wear now or 20 or 30 years from now because they&rsquo;re subtle in the pattern and they&rsquo;re not flashy and you can just wear them all the time.</p>

