<h2><em>Domestic Art</em></h2>

<p>What does a modernist have in common with an obsessive collector? The gallery owner with the artist? A metal warehouse with a chalet-style bungalow?&nbsp;<em>Domestic Art: Curated Interiors</em>&nbsp;leads you on a tour through inspiring and individualistic interiors, from a 500-square-foot bedsit to a Philip Johnson architectural wonder. Thirty-five projects in all document nearly a decade of deftly-designed and smartly-styled interiors from the pages of&nbsp;<em>PaperCity</em>&nbsp;magazine. In&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDomestic-Art-Interiors-Holly-Moore%2Fdp%2F2759403033%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Domestic Art</a></em>, a designer builds her dream home &mdash; cantilevered over an earthquake fault. A gallery owner brings a circa-1880s house back from the brink of decay and generations of nesting squirrels.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/More-is-More.webp"><img alt="More is More" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/More-is-More.webp" style="height:883px; width:736px" /></a></p>

<p><em>More is More</em></p>

<h2><em>More is More</em></h2>

<p><em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMore-Tony-Duquette-Hutton-Wilkinson%2Fdp%2F0810957027%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">More is More</a>,</em>&nbsp;the exquisite second volume about Tony Duquette, delves into the creative process and personal life of this great American designer renowned for his fantastical artwork, sculpture, jewelry, gardens, film sets, and interiors. Using &ldquo;The Enchanted Vision,&rdquo; a three-day lecture delivered by Duquette at UCLA in the early 1970s as its springboard,&nbsp;<em>More Is More</em>&nbsp;conveys through lavish illustrations Duquette&rsquo;s artistic credo on the arts of living and the living arts. Author Hutton Wilkinson explains Duquette&rsquo;s design philosophy, creative process, and studio practices, as well as the evolution of his exceptional style and vision.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/The-Well-Lived-Life.webp"><img alt="The Well Lived Life" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/The-Well-Lived-Life.webp" style="height:499px; width:357px" /></a></p>

<p><em>The Well-Lived Life</em></p>

<h2><em>The Well-Lived Life</em></h2>

<p>In the&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWell-Lived-Life-Dominique-Browning%2Fdp%2F284323445X%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">The Well-Lived Life</a>,</em>&nbsp;take an incredible look at the home-away-from home and learn how to develop the perfect interior for entertaining at your vacation home.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Vogue-Living.webp"><img alt="Vogue Living" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Vogue-Living-699x900.webp" style="height:900px; width:699px" /></a></p>

<p><em>Vogue Living: Houses, Gardens, People</em></p>

<h2><em>Vogue Living: Houses, Gardens, People</em></h2>

<p>This unique book of thirty-six spectacular houses and gardens &mdash; whose owners come from the worlds of fashion, music, art, and society &mdash; draws not only on stories that have appeared in the pages of&nbsp;<em>Vogue</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Vogue Living</em>&nbsp;over the past two decades, but also on images that have never before been published.&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FVogue-Living-Houses-Gardens-People%2Fdp%2F0307266222%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Vogue Living: Houses, Gardens, People</a></em>&nbsp;takes you to these style-makers&rsquo; private realms around the world, captured by such celebrated photographers as Miles Aldridge, Cecil Beaton, Jonathan Becker, Eric Boman, Oberto Gili, Fran&ccedil;ois Halard, Horst P. Horst, Annie Leibovitz, Sheila Metzner, Mario Testino, Tim Walker, and Bruce Weber, among many others. Their dazzling photographs bring to life interiors and exteriors, modern and classical, that are both inspiring and transporting.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/ASSOULINE-BOOK-AMERICAN-FASHION-DESIGNERS-AT-HOME.webp"><img alt="ASSOULINE BOOK AMERICAN FASHION DESIGNERS AT HOME" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/ASSOULINE-BOOK-AMERICAN-FASHION-DESIGNERS-AT-HOME-900x603.webp" style="height:603px; width:900px" /></a></p>

<p><em>American Fashion Designers at Home</em></p>

<h2><em>American Fashion Designers at Home</em></h2>

<p><em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAmerican-Fashion-Designers-at-Home%2Fdp%2F2759404714%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">American Fashion Designers at Home</a></em>&nbsp;author&nbsp;Rima Suqi has been described as having &ldquo;shopping in her soul,&rdquo; however she is about much more than just shopping. She&rsquo;s a self-proclaimed &ldquo;numbers junkie&rdquo; who has developed a keen understanding of the business behind retail through key relationships with retailers and designers. She knows it&rsquo;s not enough to be a pretty product; it&rsquo;s got to be a product that sells. For this reason, companies large and small have sought out this trend expert to help brand themselves, name their products, write press releases, brochures, catalogs and advertising copy.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Creating-a-Home.webp"><img alt="Creating a Home" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Creating-a-Home.webp" style="height:500px; width:407px" /></a></p>

<p><em>Creating a Home</em></p>

<h2><em>Creating a Home</em></h2>

<p>Kathryn M. Ireland is a maven of materials. In addition to having her own fabric line, she freely and deftly mixes other designers&rsquo; fabrics, as well as international market &ldquo;finds.&rdquo; Blending those with quality ironwork, wood, tile, and furniture pieces, Ireland pulls together a magnificent home of unpretentious grandeur. Check out her style in&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCreating-Home-Kathryn-Ireland%2Fdp%2F1423605950%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Creating a Home</a>.</em></p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Hue.webp"><img alt="Hue" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Hue-651x900.webp" style="height:900px; width:651px" /></a></p>

<p><em>Hue</em></p>

<h2><em>Hue</em></h2>

<p>Kelly Wearstler is the ultimate trendsetter in interior design.&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHue-Kelly-Wearstler%2Fdp%2F193442935X%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Hue</a></em>&nbsp;by Kelly Wearstler builds upon the success of her first monograph,&nbsp;<em>Modern Glamour</em>, and includes recent, unpublished projects, including her home in Beverly Hills, celebrity residential projects, as well as some of her latest hotel projects.&nbsp;<em>Hue</em>&nbsp;celebrates the power of color in Kelly&rsquo;s work and the possibilities of color in interior design and decorating. A must-have for amateurs and professionals seeking design inspiration from America&rsquo;s top interior designer.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Live-Love-and-Decorate.webp"><img alt="Live Love and Decorate" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Live-Love-and-Decorate-656x900.webp" style="height:900px; width:656px" /></a></p>

<p><em>Live, Love, &amp;&nbsp;Decorate</em></p>

<h2><em>Live, Love, &amp; Decorate</em></h2>

<p>For those who love boldness in design, Los Angeles-based interior designer Martyn Lawrence Bullard demonstrates his mastery of dramatic environments for a clientele of celebrities in&nbsp;<em><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMartyn-Lawrence-Bullard-Live-Love-Decorate%2Fdp%2F0847836762%3Fie%3DUTF8%26tag%3Dgentsgazette-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Live, Love, &amp; Decorate</a></em>. Drawn to glamour, Martyn Lawrence Bullard moved from London to Los Angeles to pursue acting &mdash; but became a star decorator instead. His designs balance the contemporary with the traditional, the Occidental with the ethnic. His celebrity clients&rsquo; homes are inspiring in their chic yet sumptuous styles, including Sir Elton John&rsquo;s disco-luxurious apartment with a python-skin bed, green lacquered walls, and mirrored cabinets;&nbsp;<em>Grey&rsquo;s Anatomy</em>&nbsp;star Ellen Pompeo&rsquo;s hip Mediterranean villa in the Hollywood Hills; Cher&rsquo;s residences&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;a Moorish palazzo in Malibu and a Beverly Hills Indian fantasy; and Tamara Mellon&rsquo;s New York City penthouse, which&nbsp;dazzles with bold artwork and striking color. With a knack for beautiful and dramatic spaces that don&rsquo;t sacrifice comfort, Lawrence Bullard&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;who stars in the upcoming Bravo television show &mdash;reveals his know-how for creating a sensational home.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/The-Big-Book-of-Chic.webp"><img alt="The Big Book of Chic" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/The-Big-Book-of-Chic-900x900.webp" style="height:900px; width:900px" /></a></p>

