<p>If you like 1930 style and the way we are inspired by it today, please check out my ebook,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/gentlemen-golden-age-ebook/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="">Gentlemen of the Golden Age</a>.&nbsp;Learn from the men who wore classic fashion best.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/clark-gable-gentleman-style/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Clark Gable – Gentleman of Style">Clark Gable</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/fred-astaire-gentleman-of-style/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Fred Astaire: Gentleman of Style">Fred Astaire</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/cary-grant-gentleman-style/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Cary Grant – Gentleman of Style">Cary Grant</a>&nbsp;&mdash; they all looked their best in the 1930&rsquo;s. Now you can use their source of sartorial inspiration, too.</p>

