<p><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07DRRBD87%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><img alt="got2b Spiking Glue Hair Gel" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/got2b-Spiking-Glue-Hair-Gel-1030x1030.jpeg" /></a></p>

<p><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07DRRBD87%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">got2b Spiking Glue Hair Gel</a></p>

<p>After experimenting for over 6 months, it turned out that the water-soluble spiking glue gel from g&ouml;t2b was the only gel strong enough to keep his hair in place. Interestingly, other g&ouml;t2b products did not work for him at all. He has been using the gel in the yellow tube for nearly 10 years, and his hair looks great. Even better,&nbsp;<a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07DRRBD87%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow">g&ouml;t2b Spiking Glue</a>&nbsp;is cheap and since it is made by Henkel, it should be available around the globe.</p>

<h3>Groom &amp; Clean for Thin, Straight Hair</h3>

<p><a href="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Preston-Wearing-Groom-Clean.jpg"><img alt="Preston Wearing Groom &amp; Clean" src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Preston-Wearing-Groom-Clean-1030x579.jpg" /></a></p>

<p>Preston Wearing&nbsp;<a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01IA9D8CO%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Groom &amp; Clean</a></p>

<p>Though not as well known as Brylcreem, Groom &amp; Clean is a classic product from the 1950&rsquo;s that is still a great product for men today, and it&rsquo;s the favorite of GG&rsquo;s Content Director, Preston Schlueter. Unlike it&rsquo;s more famous cousins, pomade and Brylcreem, it contains no wax and is therefore easy to wash out in a single washing.&nbsp;<a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01IA9D8CO%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow">Groom &amp; Clean</a>&nbsp;is&nbsp;an emulsion&nbsp;of water and mineral oil that also contains lanolin, a naturally derived oil, for moisture and hold. It has a pleasant but minimal scent fades quickly after application. developed in the late 50&rsquo;s; easily touched up with a wet comb</p>

<p><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01IA9D8CO%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><img alt="Groom &amp; Clean " src="https://www.gentlemansgazette.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Groom-Clean-Crop-1030x407.jpg" /></a></p>

<p><a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01IA9D8CO%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Groom &amp; Clean</a></p>

<p>It feels like a slightly tacky lotion and with a small amount, it will provide you with a light hold that is pliable all day long, or with larger amounts will result in a high shine with a medium to&nbsp;strong hold. It&rsquo;s extremely versatile and is easily washed out without any sweat or tears. Long hair or short,&nbsp;<a href="http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=12980&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01IA9D8CO%2F%3Ftag%3Dgentsgaze-20" rel="nofollow">Groom &amp; Clean</a>&nbsp;is well worth trying &ndash; and it&rsquo;s inexpensive to boot.</p>

<h2>CONCLUSION</h2>

<p>I urge you to check out the Environmental Working Group&rsquo;s Skin Deep Cosmetics Database. That is really the first step and if you go down that path, you&rsquo;ll have to invest a few hours but you&rsquo;ll be armed with more information and you know exactly what&rsquo;s good for your hair and what is not.</p>',
